==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Splenetic
<hw>Splen"e*tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spleneticus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>spl⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧tique</ets>. See
<er>Spleen</er>.]</ety> <def>Affected with spleen; malicious; spiteful;
peevish; fretful.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Splenetic</xex> guffaw.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You humor me when I am sick;⟦br⟧
Why not when I am <qex>splenetic</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Morese; gloomy; sullen; peevish;
fretful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splenetic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Splenetic
<hw>Splen"e*tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person affected with
spleen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splenetical</ent>⟦br⟧
